# Lychee link-checker ignore patterns (one regex per line).
# Configured in .github/workflows/link-check.yml (lycheeverse/lychee-action@v2).
#
# Discipline: prefer fixing broken links over adding ignore patterns. Only
# add to this file when an external URL is GENUINELY unreachable from
# CI but verified-good for human readers (e.g., resource that 403s
# unauthenticated bots but resolves in a browser).
#
# Added at v1.1.4 (CI link-checker introduction).

# Hugging Face Hub model + dataset pages sometimes 403 unauthenticated bots
# even though the resources resolve cleanly in a browser. Our HF Hub URLs
# include BBehring/prompt-injection-{lora,frozen-probe,full-ft,tfidf-lr} +
# the upstream dataset pages (deepset, lakera, lmsys, hackaprompt, etc.).
^https://huggingface\.co/.*$

# GitHub anchor links (file.md#section-anchor) sometimes resolve at the file
# level but lychee's fragment-checking against rendered HTML can flag false
# positives because GitHub generates slug-cased anchors from markdown headers
# at render time. Allow file-level GH URLs through; anchors get verified
# at site-render via Quarto's own link-checker (run via `make site`).
^https://github\.com/brandon-behring/prompt-injection-detection-prototype/blob/.*#.*$
^https://github\.com/brandon-behring/prompt-injection-detection-prototype/tree/.*#.*$

# Note (v1.2.2): the 14 broken slug-ref patterns previously listed here were
# DELETED after v1.2.2 Commit 2 applied ADR-067's narrow immutability
# relaxation to fix the broken refs in-place across the affected ADRs.
# Future broken-slug-refs should be FIXED IN-PLACE per ADR-067 + commit
# message convention; do NOT add new ignore patterns for internal ADR
# cross-refs. External-URL ignore patterns (HF Hub bot-403s; GH anchor
# false-positives) remain above as they have a different rationale.

# Historical scholarly/vendor references in immutable ADRs. Current
# reader-facing docs should use stable replacements instead of adding here.
^https://www\.acm\.org/publications/policies/artifact-review-and-badging-current$
^https://www\.researchgate\.net/publication/.*$
^https://ojs\.aaai\.org/index\.php/AAAI/article/view/9602$
^https://platform\.openai\.com/docs/deprecations$
^https://platform\.openai\.com/docs/models/gpt-4o$
^https://openai\.com/api/pricing/?$

# Exact DOI citations from immutable ADRs whose DOI resolver redirects to
# publisher pages that 403 unauthenticated CI bots. DOI targets remain the
# canonical human-readable citation form; keep this list exact, not broad.
^https://doi\.org/10\.1177/0956797613504966$
^https://doi\.org/10\.1080/00031305\.2016\.1154108$
^https://doi\.org/10\.1198/000313006X152649$
^https://doi\.org/10\.1177/001316446002000104$
^https://doi\.org/10\.2307/2529310$
^https://doi\.org/10\.1145/1143844\.1143874$
^https://doi\.org/10\.2307/2531595$
^https://doi\.org/10\.1080/01621459\.2023\.2197686$
^https://doi\.org/10\.2307/2290993$

# Specific historical 404s retained only in immutable ADR citation fields.
# Fix mutable docs in-place; do not broaden these patterns without a concrete
# lychee failure and a note explaining why the reference is historical.
^https://neurips\.cc/Conferences/2024/PaperInformation/PaperChecklist$
^https://scikit-learn\.org/stable/tutorial/text_analytics/working_with_text_data\.html$
^https://arxiv\.org/abs/2311\.18964$
^https://www\.cs\.cmu\.edu/~aarti/Class/10704_Spring15/Niculescu-Mizil_Caruana\.pdf$
^https://www\.cs\.iastate\.edu/~honavar/elkan\.pdf$
^https://github\.com/Microsoft/calibration/Kull-2017-Beta-calibration$
^https://www\.jstor\.org/stable/27033529$

# v1.2.13 tag URL referenced from reader-facing surfaces (README, WRITEUP,
# READING_GUIDE) before the tag itself lands at C7 of the v1.2.13 patch
# sequence. Chicken-and-egg from auto-continue-on-CI-green discipline: C2
# updates the "Current state" URLs but the tag is created at C7. The pattern
# resolves to a real URL after v1.2.13 is tagged; safe to keep here (or
# remove on next housekeeping commit).
^https://github\.com/brandon-behring/prompt-injection-detection-prototype/tree/v1\.2\.13$
